2:T46a,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Are spinal adjustments safe?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. When performed by a certified clinical physiotherapist like Dr. Rohit Verma, manual adjustments are extremely safe. We perform a thorough screening to rule out contraindications like osteoporosis first."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What causes the clicking sound during chiropractic care?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The sound is called cavitation. It is simply the release of gas bubbles (nitrogen) from the joint fluid when the joint space is gently opened, reducing internal pressure."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What are Dry Needling and Cupping Therapy, and how do they help?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Dry Needling uses sterile single-use needles to release painful trigger points (muscle knots), while Cupping Therapy uses suction cups to increase blood flow and relieve fascial tension. Both are highly effective when combined with manual chiropractic adjustments to speed up pain relief and muscle recovery."}}]}0:{"rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"w-full max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 md:py-16 text-left","children":[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$2"}}],["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BreadcrumbList\",\"itemListElement\":[{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":1,\"name\":\"Home\",\"item\":\"https://physioventure.pages.dev\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":2,\"name\":\"Services\",\"item\":\"https://physioventure.pages.dev/services/\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":3,\"name\":\"Chiropractic & Manual Therapy\",\"item\":\"https://physioventure.pages.dev/services/chiropractic-manual-therapy/\"}]}"}}],["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dange